+ Switching to a Different Schema
+ Title 2
+-+-+

+-+-+
+ Switching to a Different Schema
+-+-+
	Instead of execute synonyms for each query
	e.g. SELECT * FROM COMPANYSCHEMA.TABLE_NAME; 
	it's possible to set the default schema with the command:

	ALTER SESSION SET CURRENT_SCHEMA = COMPANYSCHEMA;

	After that it's possible to execute queries without synonyms
	e.g. SELECT * FROM TABLE_NAME;

